headline: GWW Q1 Earnings Call: Tariffs and Supply Chain Uncertainty Shape Outlook Despite Steady Results
summary: Maintenance and repair supplier W.W. Grainger (NYSE:GWW) met Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q1 CY2025, with sales up 1.7% year on year to $4.31 billion. On the other hand, the company’s full-year revenue guidance of $17.85 billion at the midpoint came in 0.7% below analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $9.86 per share was 3.6% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
